Good Material & Good Construction. 1. What is Tin-plated copper wire? A thin layer of tin is plated on the surface of the copper wire. It looks silver. It has good electrical conductivity, Compared with bare copper wire stronger corrosion resistance and oxidation resistance, which can greatly extend the service life of the wire. 2. What is 1007 wire? 1007 wire is a kind of electronic wire, which is the internal wiring of electrical equipment. The insulating layer uses PVC material; The conductor uses copper wire or tinned copper wire (ZLKSKER wires all use tinned copper wire); Rated temperature: 80°C; Rated voltage: 300V; Pass UL VW-1 flame resistance test. 3. 18AWG (American Wire Gauge) wire standard: Conductor diameter 1.02mm; Cross-sectional area: 0.81mm²; Wire outer diameter 2.0mm.
Low resistance, strong conductivity. Corrosion and oxidation resistance. Stable current and safer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I haven’t had any problems with my motherboard or power supply

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 20, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good Quality Cable
reviews.reviewText: The original power supply on the Lenovo E73 starts to fail. I can smell bad burning smell plastic. Just do not want to wait for the PS to fry your entire motherboard + CPU.It is a pity that Lenovo does not use regular power supply. So we either have to get rid of the PC, or to get another Lenovo power supply. So a adaptor cable with a standard power supply is acceptable.This cable does the job well. The cable is braided and that is very good. The length is just perfect.This is just an one time purchase since we won't need such cable again. It is a good item and good quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The results alleviated my initial concerns..
reviews.reviewText: I'll admit, I was a little concerned about reducing 24 pins down to 14 without having some kind of adverse affect. But I've been running/testing a Lenovo P410 for a few weeks and now have the feeling that the system could care less about being powered by a standard ATX power supply vs the crazy minimal and proprietary (but Platinum!) 14 pin FSP/Lenovo version. Extremely happy and relieved that this actually works, even though I don't understand how. Very high quality part.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It was what I needed
reviews.reviewText: I had a bunch of spare parts laying around and wanted to use a higher wattage power-supply than was in the old computer. I needed to convert the 24-pin power to 14, and this did exactly that. I chose one that had the casing on it because it looked cleaner inside my case. It came when expected and was extremely easy to use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 28, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Plug and play. Bought for Lenovo H50.
reviews.reviewText: I recently upgraded my stock PSU to a modular Corsair 650w and I needed a 24 to 14 pin cable. I ordered this one and it is working well. I deducted one star because the item that arrived did not have a cable sleeve as pictured. It is not a big deal, but if the cable supplied had the cable sleeve as pictured it definitely helps with cable management within the compact computer case. I had to use extra zip ties to secure the extended (longer) cable away from the motherboard and other hardware.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Using this cable allows easy upgrade of Think Server TS140 power supply for power hungry GPU
reviews.reviewText: Upgraded to 650W power supply to add an MSI GeForce RTX 3060 VENTUS 2X OC Graphics Card in my TS140. Had to remove the motherboard cable for the front USB ports to slot the card. Also needed a right angle 8-pin power connector for the card to be able to close the case.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 29, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works for Lenovo Erazer X315
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this for an older lenovo pc. The power supply blew but luckily didn't take the whole computer with it. Lenovo pcs take a proprietary power supply that cost double what a standard power supply does. Using this adapter I was able to easily install a standard power supply in the pc that worked perfectly with this adapter. My adapter did come with the wire cover on it. Hopefully others will see this and save their money buy using this adapter.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Does the job!

reviews.reviewText: I used it on my Lenovo and it worked perfectly first try

reviews.reviewTitle: Pin Voltage is a perfect match for ThinkCentre M83
reviews.reviewText: I bought a refurbished Lenovo ThinkCentre M83 Tower in 2021. It came with a Huntkey HK380-16FP Power Supply with a 14-pins Motherboard connector and a 4-pins CPU connector. Since I want to add a graphic card that requires power, I had to change the PSU (AresGame 500W, standard PSU). Before plugging this adapter in the motherboard, I used my multimeter to check all the pin voltages. It's a perfect match. It's with great confidence that I plugged everything and flipped the switch on. Working great so far.

reviews.reviewTitle: Works as intended, it’s quite long though
Works great and is very nice quality
reviews.reviewText: I bought this so I could put a standard power supply into a Thinkcentre. Everything snapped into place easily. The adapter is made from decent quality materials and feels sturdy. The wiring was correct as well. Would recommend
Be sure to do some pre bending as my cable was very very stiff. It can very easily put a lot of pressure/tension on the 14 pin female board connector
